#. <section class="sutta" id="an4.28"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an4.28:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 4"
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 4"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "an4.28:0.2"
msgid "3. Uruvelavagga"
msgstr "3. At Uruvelā"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "an4.28:0.3"
msgid "28. Ariyavaṃsasutta"
msgstr "28. The Noble Traditions"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "an4.28:1.1"
msgid ""
"“Cattārome, bhikkhave, ariyavaṃsā aggaññā rattaññā vaṃsaññā porāṇā asaṃkiṇṇā "
"asaṃkiṇṇapubbā, na saṅkīyanti na saṅkīyissanti, appaṭikuṭṭhā samaṇehi "
"brāhmaṇehi viññūhi."
msgstr ""
"“Mendicants, these four noble traditions are original, long-standing, "
"traditional, and ancient. They are uncorrupted, as they have been since the "
"beginning. They’re not being corrupted now, nor will they be. Sensible "
"ascetics and brahmins don’t look down on them."

msgctxt "an4.28:1.2"
msgid "Katame cattāro?"
msgstr "What four?"

#. VAR: agadhito → agathito (bj, pts1)
msgctxt "an4.28:1.3"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu santuṭṭho hoti itarītarena cīvarena, "
"itarītaracīvarasantuṭṭhiyā ca vaṇṇavādī, na ca cīvarahetu anesanaṃ "
"appatirūpaṃ āpajjati, aladdhā ca cīvaraṃ na paritassati, laddhā ca cīvaraṃ "
"agadhito amucchito anajjhosanno ādīnavadassāvī nissaraṇapañño paribhuñjati;"
msgstr ""
"Firstly, a mendicant is content with any kind of robe, and praises such "
"contentment. They don’t try to get hold of a robe in an improper way. They "
"don’t get upset if they don’t get a robe. And if they do get a robe, they "
"use it untied, unstupefied, unattached, seeing the drawback, and "
"understanding the escape."

msgctxt "an4.28:1.4"
msgid ""
"tāya ca pana itarītaracīvarasantuṭṭhiyā nevattānukkaṃseti, no paraṃ vambheti."
msgstr ""
"But they don’t glorify themselves or put others down on account of their "
"contentment."

msgctxt "an4.28:1.5"
msgid ""
"Yo hi tattha dakkho analaso sampajāno patissato, ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, "
"bhikkhu porāṇe aggaññe ariyavaṃse ṭhito."
msgstr ""
"A mendicant who is expert, tireless, aware, and mindful in this is said to "
"stand in the ancient, original noble tradition."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli2.28"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "an4.28:2.1"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, bhikkhu santuṭṭho hoti itarītarena piṇḍapātena, "
"itarītarapiṇḍapātasantuṭṭhiyā ca vaṇṇavādī, na ca piṇḍapātahetu anesanaṃ "
"appatirūpaṃ āpajjati, aladdhā ca piṇḍapātaṃ na paritassati, laddhā ca "
"piṇḍapātaṃ agadhito amucchito anajjhosanno ādīnavadassāvī nissaraṇapañño "
"paribhuñjati;"
msgstr "Furthermore, a mendicant is content with any kind of alms-food …"

msgctxt "an4.28:2.2"
msgid ""
"tāya ca pana itarītarapiṇḍapātasantuṭṭhiyā nevattānukkaṃseti, no paraṃ "
"vambheti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an4.28:2.3"
msgid ""
"Yo hi tattha dakkho analaso sampajāno patissato, ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, "
"bhikkhu porāṇe aggaññe ariyavaṃse ṭhito."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "an4.28:3.1"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, bhikkhu santuṭṭho hoti itarītarena senāsanena, "
"itarītarasenāsanasantuṭṭhiyā ca vaṇṇavādī, na ca senāsanahetu anesanaṃ "
"appatirūpaṃ āpajjati, aladdhā ca senāsanaṃ na paritassati, laddhā ca "
"senāsanaṃ agadhito amucchito anajjhosanno ādīnavadassāvī nissaraṇapañño "
"paribhuñjati;"
msgstr "Furthermore, a mendicant is content with any kind of lodgings …"

msgctxt "an4.28:3.2"
msgid ""
"tāya ca pana itarītarasenāsanasantuṭṭhiyā nevattānukkaṃseti, no paraṃ "
"vambheti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an4.28:3.3"
msgid ""
"Yo hi tattha dakkho analaso sampajāno patissato, ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, "
"bhikkhu porāṇe aggaññe ariyavaṃse ṭhito."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "an4.28:4.1"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, bhikkhu bhāvanārāmo hoti bhāvanārato, pahānārāmo "
"hoti pahānarato;"
msgstr ""
"Furthermore, a mendicant enjoys meditation and loves to meditate. They enjoy "
"giving up and love to give up."

msgctxt "an4.28:4.2"
msgid ""
"tāya ca pana bhāvanārāmatāya bhāvanāratiyā pahānārāmatāya pahānaratiyā "
"nevattānukkaṃseti, no paraṃ vambheti."
msgstr ""
"But they don’t glorify themselves or put down others on account of their "
"love for meditation and giving up."

msgctxt "an4.28:4.3"
msgid ""
"Yo hi tattha dakkho analaso sampajāno patissato, ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, "
"bhikkhu porāṇe aggaññe ariyavaṃse ṭhito."
msgstr ""
"A mendicant who is expert, tireless, aware, and mindful in this is said to "
"stand in the ancient, original noble tradition."

msgctxt "an4.28:4.4"
msgid ""
"Ime kho, bhikkhave, cattāro ariyavaṃsā aggaññā rattaññā vaṃsaññā porāṇā "
"asaṅkiṇṇā asaṅkiṇṇapubbā, na saṅkīyanti na saṅkīyissanti, appaṭikuṭṭhā "
"samaṇehi brāhmaṇehi viññūhi."
msgstr ""
"These four noble traditions are original, long-standing, traditional, and "
"ancient. They are uncorrupted, as they have been since the beginning. They’"
"re not being corrupted now nor will they be. Sensible ascetics and brahmins "
"don’t look down on them."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "an4.28:5.1"
msgid ""
"Imehi ca pana, bhikkhave, catūhi ariyavaṃsehi samannāgato bhikkhu "
"puratthimāya cepi disāya viharati sveva aratiṃ sahati, na taṃ arati sahati;"
msgstr ""
"When a mendicant has these four noble traditions, if they live in the east "
"they beat discontent, and discontent doesn’t beat them."

msgctxt "an4.28:5.2"
msgid ""
"pacchimāya cepi disāya viharati sveva aratiṃ sahati, na taṃ arati sahati;"
msgstr "If they live in the west …"

msgctxt "an4.28:5.3"
msgid "uttarāya cepi disāya viharati sveva aratiṃ sahati, na taṃ arati sahati;"
msgstr "the north …"

msgctxt "an4.28:5.4"
msgid ""
"dakkhiṇāya cepi disāya viharati sveva aratiṃ sahati, na taṃ arati sahati."
msgstr "the south, they beat discontent, and discontent doesn’t beat them."

msgctxt "an4.28:5.5"
msgid "Taṃ kissa hetu?"
msgstr "Why is that?"

msgctxt "an4.28:5.6"
msgid "Aratiratisaho hi, bhikkhave, dhīroti."
msgstr "Because a stable person prevails over desire and discontent."

#. </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc6"></a>
#. VAR: dhīraṃ → vīraṃ (bj)
msgctxt "an4.28:6.1"
msgid "Nārati sahati dhīraṃ,"
msgstr "Dissatisfaction doesn’t beat a stable one;"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an4.28:6.2"
msgid "nārati dhīraṃ sahati;"
msgstr "for the stable one is not beaten by discontent."

#. <br>
msgctxt "an4.28:6.3"
msgid "Dhīrova aratiṃ sahati,"
msgstr "A stable person beats discontent,"

# So, you do better.
#. <br>
msgctxt "an4.28:6.4"
msgid "dhīro hi aratissaho."
msgstr "for the stable one is a beater of discontent."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli2.29"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc7"></a>
msgctxt "an4.28:7.1"
msgid "Sabbakammavihāyīnaṃ,"
msgstr "Who can hold back the dispeller,"

#. <br>
#. VAR: panuṇṇaṃ → panunnaṃ (bj) | paṇunnaṃ (?)
msgctxt "an4.28:7.2"
msgid "panuṇṇaṃ ko nivāraye;"
msgstr "who’s thrown away all karma?"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an4.28:7.3"
msgid "Nekkhaṃ jambonadasseva,"
msgstr "They’re like a coin of mountain gold:"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an4.28:7.4"
msgid "ko taṃ ninditumarahati;"
msgstr "who is worthy of criticizing them?"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an4.28:7.5"
msgid "Devāpi naṃ pasaṃsanti,"
msgstr "Even the gods praise them,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an4.28:7.6"
msgid "brahmunāpi pasaṃsito”ti."
msgstr "and by Brahmā, too, they’re praised.”"

#. </p></blockquote><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an4.28:7.7"
msgid "Aṭṭhamaṃ."
msgstr ""
